Task: Make trait with async methods dyn compatible (object safe)?

 <p>I coded an app that should sync git repos to our company's network hosts. Since I'm also testing the facilities I thought I'd naturally use the strategy pattern and have the executing function use different strategies in tests (noop) and in production as this is a common pattern in other programming languages. Now I want to make it async, but there's the catch. It seems I can't have traits with async functions.</p>
<p>This is the trait we're speaking of that is implemented differently in test and production:</p>
<pre><code>pub trait RemoteActions
{
    async fn change_path(&amp;mut self, from: &amp;Path, to: &amp;Path) -&gt; anyhow::Result&lt;()&gt;;

    async fn remove_repo(&amp;mut self, path: &amp;Path) -&gt; anyhow::Result&lt;()&gt;;

    async fn add_repo(&amp;mut self, path: &amp;Path) -&gt; anyhow::Result&lt;()&gt;;

    fn get_element(&amp;self, num: usize) -&gt; anyhow::Result&lt;String&gt;;
}
</code></pre>
<p>But rust-analyzer is complaining:</p>
<pre><code>rustc: for a trait to be dyn compatible it needs to allow building a vtable                                  
│
┃   4 ┊   async fn add_repo(&amp;mut self, path: &amp;Path) -&gt; anyhow::Result&lt;(│   for more information, visit &lt;https://doc.rust-lang.org/reference/items/traits.html#dyn-compatibility&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>How do I make it dyn compatible? What's the Rust way of going about that?</p>


